# ðŸ§  TRIDENT Development Workflow

To keep our codebase clean and collaborative, we follow a **branch-based workflow**.  
This ensures that new features, bug fixes, and releases are easy to manage.

---

## ðŸ”± Branch Naming Convention

| Type | Naming Pattern | Example |
|------|----------------|----------|
| Main Branch | `main` | Main stable release branch |
| Feature | `feature/<short-description>` | feature/payment-gateway |
| Bug Fix | `fix/<short-description>` | fix/settings-page-alignment |
| Hotfix (urgent) | `hotfix/<short-description>` | hotfix/api-crash |
| Release | `release/<version>` | release/v1.2.0 |

---

## ðŸŒ¿ Workflow Steps

1. **Create a new branch** before starting any work:
   ```bash
   git checkout main
   git pull origin main
   git checkout -b feature/add-dashboard-ui
Make changes, test your code locally, and commit often:

bash
Copy code
git add .
git commit -m "Add animated dashboard UI with glassmorphism"
